\section{[[acid: startstop()]]}

%claude:
[<startstop()>] is the most important process control builtin:
it resumes the target and blocks until the target stops again
(at a breakpoint, fault, or system call). This is the core
of the ``continue until something happens'' operation.
After the target stops, it reads pending notes and calls
the [[stopped]] callback.

<<function [[startstop]]>>=
void
startstop(Node *r, Node *args)
{
    Node res;

    USED(r);
    if(args == nil)
        error("startstop(pid): no pid");
    expr(args, &res);
    if(res.type != TINT)
        error("startstop(pid): arg type");

    msg(res.ival, "startstop");

    notes(res.ival);
    dostop(res.ival);
}
@

